 People residing in the village are unable to enter or leave the location at this stage. The protesters have banded together across the street from the entrance to a new mine in the area. The demonstrators are unhappy about the new mine not providing work opportunities to local residents. According to reports from locals in the area, the Stoffberg Road is open for use, however, it is suspected that the protesters may block the road at a later stage. Motorists are urged to proceed with caution.     Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za